Here is the converted `pom.xml` for the Spring Boot application, compatible with JDK 8 and using Apache Tomcat as the embedded servlet container. The configuration has been updated to remove WebLogic-specific elements and to include Spring Boot dependencies.

### Converted `pom.xml`:


<project xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0" 
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" 
         xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd">
    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>
    <parent>
        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-parent</artifactId>
        <version>1.5.22.RELEASE</version> <!-- Latest 1.x version compatible with JDK 8 -->
        <relativePath/> <!-- lookup parent from repository -->
    </parent>
    <artifactId>jee-example-app</artifactId>
    <name>JEE Example App</name>
    <packaging>war</packaging>
    
    <properties>
        <java.version>1.8</java.version>
    </properties>

    <dependencies>
        <dependency>
            <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
            <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-web</artifactId>
        </dependency>
        <dependency>
            <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
            <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-data-jpa</artifactId>
        </dependency>
        <dependency>
            <groupId>org.apache.commons</groupId>
            <artifactId>commons-lang3</artifactId>
            <version>3.12.0</version> <!-- Updated version of Commons Lang -->
        </dependency>
        <dependency>
            <groupId>org.windup.example</groupId>
            <artifactId>jee-example-services</artifactId>
            <version>1.0.0</version>
            <scope>compile</scope>
        </dependency>
        <dependency>
            <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
            <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-tomcat</artifactId>
            <scope>provided</scope> <!-- Use embedded Tomcat -->
        </dependency>
    </dependencies>

    <build>
        <plugins>
            <plugin>
                <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
                <artifactId>spring-boot-maven-plugin</artifactId>
            </plugin>
        </plugins>
    </build>
</project>


### Key Changes Made:
1. **Parent Block**: Added the `spring-boot-starter-parent` as the parent for dependency management.
2. **Dependencies**: 
   - Replaced `javaee-api` with `spring-boot-starter-web` and `spring-boot-starter-data-jpa`.
   - Updated `commons-lang` to `commons-lang3`.
   - Removed WebLogic-specific dependencies and configurations.
3. **Packaging**: Kept the packaging as `war` to maintain compatibility with the original structure.
4. **Tomcat**: Added `spring-boot-starter-tomcat` for embedded Tomcat support.
5. **Java Version**: Specified the Java version as a property for clarity.

This `pom.xml` is now ready for a Spring Boot application, allowing for a smooth transition from the legacy WebLogic environment. 

